Switch/toggle buttons must always have the thumb properly contained within the track — never overflowing. Always verify sizing math (track height vs thumb height, translate distance vs remaining space).
In RTL interfaces, always test switches in the checked state too; prefer flex alignment + overflow-hidden over translate-only movement so the thumb never exits the track.
The shared Switch component at src/components/ui/switch.tsx is already RTL-safe (uses flex justify + overflow-hidden, no translate). Do NOT regress it back to translate-x. If you need a custom toggle, follow the same pattern: overflow-hidden track, thumb positioned via data-[state=checked]:justify-end / justify-start.
